<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Caldyen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hail everyone!<P>I am a resident of the Povar server, in a "small close-knit group of friends" type of guild.  As such, I dont keep much communcation with the higher level guilds on our server.<P>What I would like to know is which guilds are usually open to guests on raids, and I would also like to know how Ragefire is handled on our server.<P>Thank you for your time...<P><P>------------------<BR>Caldyen Nightblade<BR>54th Rank Cleric of Tunare<BR>Officer of Providence<BR>Bearer of the Aegis of Life<P>Povar</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lladra</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">RF=FFA<P>And I think Aquilo is usually open to guests, not sure though.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Elayne Trakand</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Most don't take invites unless they are applying for the guild.  Some will though, but it usually means you're not allowed to roll on any loot that drops.<P>Reasons are cause most have a merit system in place already and obviously guild members have more merit then non-guild invites.  Also large guilds don't progress to become large if they are equipping other people outside the guild.<P>If your just wanting the experience of doing a higher end raid then I'd talk to Asatru, The Guardian Lords or Utopian perhaps.  They aren't Uber guilds but most likely raiding higher level stuff then your guild.  Not sure on their policies though.<P>As for Rage, it used to be who was in the lair first got it first and there was usually always two or three waiting in line.  Leave the lair loose the camp, but there were always those that didn't like waiting in lines.  Since the change though best bet is to just go there and start camping it, talk with those that are currently or recently done Rage.<P>Hope this helps<P>Elayne Trakand<BR>High Priest<BR>Blades of Law<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Chronomis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, I can tell you how it was handled by my guild.  Sanctus Covenir started camping even before our turn came around.  We were there with our cleric and often multiple people killing the fire giants can keeping various sites in SolB heavily camped, even while the previous cleric held the camp.  When Serrath of Blades of Law got his epic, we simply kept right on camping, maintaining not only our cleric in the dungeon, but keeping all the giants cleared out as they popped and usually keeping SS camped as well.  During our camp it was probably a fairly rare occasion for our guild members not to be the majority of people in the dungeon.  We had to deal with Naggy once, which was done through an invitational raid, and eventually we got Ragefire and our cleric got her epic, the first in our guild and I believe the last under the old quest on Povar.<P>I would say, though, that with the changes to the end of the quest this approach would likely have some problems.  Keeping half of Skyfire camped is a much bigger problem than doing the same with SolB.<P>Chronomis - 52 Druid<BR>Tontom - 36 Cleric<BR>Sanctus Covenir, Povar<BR></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
